ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Have you ever used hormones or hormone blockers for medical transition or gender affirmation?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 777= I prefer not to answer; 999= Do not know

Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 777= I prefer not to answer; 999= Do not know

ElementDescription: Some people use complimentary or alternative medicine (CAM) such as herbs, supplements, acupuncture, etc. for gender affirmation. Which of the following statements is the most true for you?
Notes: 1 = I am currently using CAM for gender affirmation; 2 = I have used CAM for gender affirmation, but am not currently using CAM; 3 = I have not used CAM for gender affirmation, but I would like to use CAM; 4 = I have not used CAM for gender affirmation, and I am not interested in CAM; 777 = I prefer not to answer; 999 Don't know
